.SH NAME
octane-cache-prune - Remove cache entries older than --max-age


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoctane cache prune [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
prune removes entries whose WrittenAt plus max-age is before now,
and entries whose TTL has expired.

.PP
Empty fanout directories are removed after pruning.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for prune

.PP
\fB--max-age\fP=24h0m0s
	maximum age of cache entries to keep (e.g. 24h, 7d)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--cache-dir\fP=""
	override the cache directory (default: $XDG_CACHE_HOME/octane/cache)

.PP
\fB--config\fP="octane.yml"
	path to octane.yml configuration file

.PP
\fB--no-cache\fP[=false]
	bypass the result cache entirely

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	enable verbose output


